The course consists of six lectures about teaching methods on Estonian, and related individual excercises that are presented in six seminars: analysis of curricula, planning of teaching modules, planning of lessons, basic methods of teaching literacy, designing practice tasks, and giving feedback.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is to provide students the comprehensive overview of literacy teaching methods, to hel students to develop skills of planning literacy teaching at all levels; and to practice planning of teaching at all levels (curricula, study plans, lesson plans, lesson scripts, excercises and assessment).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students successfully completing the course have acquired the main teaching methods of Estonian literacy, and the principles of feedback and assessment. They are able to plan teaching of Estonian literacy at all levels (curricula, study plans, lesson plans, lesson scripts, excercises and assessment).
